  "gold_answer": "7",
  "generated_text": "To find the total number of dozens of eggs Claire eats in 4 weeks, we need to break down the problem into steps:\n\n1.  **Calculate the number of eggs eaten per week:**\n    Claire makes 3 egg omelets every morning. Assuming she eats one omelet per day, she eats 3 eggs per day.\n    There are 7 days in a week.\n    $$ \\text{Eggs per week} = 3 \\text{ eggs/day} \\times 7 \\text{ days/week} = 21 \\text{ eggs} $$\n\n2.  **Calculate the number of eggs eaten in 4 weeks:**\n    $$ \\text{Total eggs} = 21 \\text{ eggs/week} \\times 4 \\text{ weeks} = 84 \\text{ eggs} $$\n\n3.  **Convert the total number of eggs to dozens:**\n    There are 12 eggs in one dozen.\n    $$ \\text{Total dozens} = \\frac{84 \\text{ eggs}}{12 \\text{ eggs/dozen}} = 7 \\text{ dozens} $$\n\n**Work:**\n*   Eggs per week: $3 \\times 7 = 21$\n*   Eggs in 4 weeks: $21 \\times 4 = 84$\n*   Dozens of eggs: $84 / 12 = 7$\n\n\\boxed{7}\n",
